gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Magic 98, Knicks 94
gameRecap.excerpt: The Magic closed the game on a 17-6 run and defeated the Knicks, 98-94. Paolo Banchero recorded 20 points, six rebounds, and three assists for the Magic, with Wendell Carter Jr. adding 17 points and three rebounds in the victory. Miles McBride tallied 20 points and two rebounds for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Magic improve to 22-18 in the regular season, while the Knicks fall to 23-17.
